nand-mahindra-reacts-4734333%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fviral-video-wed-be-bankrupt-noida-boy-wants-to-buy-thar-for-rs-700-anand-mahindra-reacts-4734333%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fviral-video-wed-be-bankrupt-noida-boy-wants-to-buy-thar-for-rs-700-anand-mahindra-reacts-4734333%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Is%20the%20IMA%20Cheering%20If%20Doctors%20Are%20Still%20Punishable%20for%20Medical%20Negligence%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F01124355%2FDYF-camp.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%2022%20December%2C%20the%20Indian%20Medical%20Association%20(IMA)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20largest%20organisation%20representing%20doctors%20in%20the%20country%20%E2%80%93%20extended%20its%20gratitude%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Union%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20via%20a%20daily%20newspaper%20advertisement%20for%20%E2%80%9Cexempting%20medical%20professionals%20from%20criminal%20prosecution%20under%20304(a)%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20now%2026%20of%20BNS%20(death%20by%20rash%20or%20negligent%20act).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20gesture%20followed%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20announcement%20in%20Parliament%2C%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20while%20the%20three%20criminal%20reform%20Bills%20were%20passed%2C%20assuring%20that%20the%20provisions%20related%20to%20death%20resulting%20from%20medical%20negligence%20would%20be%20excluded%20from%20Section%2026%20of%20the%20new%20Bill%20%E2%80%93%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20(BNS).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20pledged%20an%20amendment%20to%20shield%20doctors%20from%20potential%20legal%20repercussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoctors%20not%20exempt%20from%20punishment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20after%20the%20Bill%E2%80%99s%20passage%20in%20both%20Houses%2C%20it%20became%20evident%20that%20doctors%20don%E2%80%99t%20actually%20receive%20outright%20immunity%20in%20cases%20of%20death%20due%20to%20negligence%20under%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20BNS.%20Instead%2C%20the%20legislation%20maintains%20a%20maximum%20two-year%20imprisonment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%2C%20though%2C%20is%20that%20this%20is%20a%20slightly%20reduced%20penalty%20compared%20to%20other%20death-related%20offences%2C%20the%20punishments%20for%20which%20have%20been%20increased.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20BNS%2C%20the%20punishment%20for%20causing%20accidental%20death%20(like%20road%20traffic%20death)%20was%20increased%20to%20a%20maximum%20of%20five%20years.%20An%20additional%20provision%20was%20introduced%20for%20situations%20where%20the%20responsible%20party%20flees%20or%20fails%20to%20report%20the%20incident%2C%20allowing%20for%20imprisonment%20of%20up%20to%2010%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20amendment%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20such%20an%20act%20is%20done%20by%20a%20registered%20medical%20practitioner%20while%20performing%20a%20medical%20procedure%2C%20he%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20imprisonment%20of%20either%20description%20for%20a%20term%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20two%20years%2C%20and%20shall%20also%20be%20liable%20to%20a%20fine.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20essence%2C%20criminal%20cases%20can%20still%20be%20filed%20against%20medical%20professionals%20for%20deaths%20arising%20from%20medical%20negligence%2C%20but%20the%20maximum%20imprisonment%20is%20now%20less%20severe%20compared%20to%20other%20death-related%20scenarios.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20why%20is%20the%20IMA%20happy%20about%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amendment%20will%20maintain%20the%20maximum%20imprisonment%20for%20doctors%20at%20the%20same%20level%20as%20specified%20under%20Section%20304(A)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%2C%20allowing%20for%20up%20to%20two%20years%20of%20imprisonment%20and%20a%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20original%20draft%20of%20the%20Bill%20had%20asked%20for%20seven%20years%20of%20punishment%20for%20death%20due%20to%20negligence.%20We%20made%20a%20submission%20to%20the%20parliamentary%20committee%20to%20differentiate%20medical%20death%20by%20a%20doctor%20from%20death%20due%20to%20negligence.%20Later%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20lowered%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20President-elect%20of%20IMA%2C%20Dr%20V%20Asokan%2C%20to%C2%A0%3Cstrong%3ESouth%20First%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20Home%20Minister%20accepted%20the%20demand%20and%20differentiated%20medical%20negligence.%20%E2%80%9CMoreover%2C%20the%20minister%20went%20beyond%20this%20in%20the%20parliamentary%20proceedings%2C%20explicitly%20stating%20that%20deaths%20during%20treatment%20were%20no%20longer%20to%20be%20considered%20as%20murder.%20The%20minister%20expressed%20the%20intention%20to%20exempt%20doctors%20from%20such%20scenarios%20through%20an%20upcoming%20amendment%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Asokan%20added%20that%20the%20parliamentary%20declaration%20by%20the%20Home%20Minister%20signifies%20a%20departure%20from%20previous%20norms%2C%20affirming%20that%20any%20death%20during%20treatment%20is%20not%20to%20be%20deemed%20as%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20essence%2C%20the%20government%20has%20declared%2C%20in%20principle%2C%20its%20acceptance%20of%20the%20IMA%E2%80%99s%20stance%20that%20there%20is%20no%20criminality%20involved%20in%20the%20relationship%20between%20a%20doctor%20and%20a%20patient.%20The%20IMA%20has%20consistently%20maintained%20that%20there%20is%20no%20criminal%20intention%20between%20a%20doctor%20and%20a%20patient%2C%20emphasising%20that%20criminality%20requires%20intent%20to%20harm%2C%20and%20crime%20is%20defined%20by%20the%20presence%20of%20criminal%20intent%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Dr%20Asokan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMedical%20negligence%20as%20per%20the%20Jacob%20Mathew%20case%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMedical%20negligence%20is%20subject%20to%20provisions%20influenced%20by%20case%20laws%2C%20particularly%20relevant%20Supreme%20Court%20judgements%20like%20Jacob%20Mathew%20vs%20State%20of%20Punjab%2C%20dealing%20with%20medical%20negligence%20and%20the%20criminal%20liability%20of%20doctors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20heard%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20and%20resulted%20in%20the%20formulation%20of%20important%20guidelines%20regarding%20the%20prosecution%20of%20doctors%20for%20offences%20related%20to%20medical%20negligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20involved%20a%20doctor%2C%20Jacob%20Mathew%2C%20accused%20of%20causing%20a%20patient%E2%80%99s%20death%20due%20to%20medical%20negligence.%20Dr%20Mathew%20challenged%20criminal%20proceedings%2C%20arguing%20that%20a%20medical%20professional%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20held%20criminally%20liable%20for%20an%20error%20of%20judgement%20or%20a%20bona%20fide%20mistake%20while%20treating%20a%20patient.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20its%202005%20judgment%2C%20acknowledged%20the%20need%20to%20protect%20doctors%20from%20frivolous%20criminal%20prosecutions%20but%20emphasised%20accountability%20in%20cases%20of%20genuine%20medical%20negligence.%20The%20court%20laid%20down%20guidelines%20to%20differentiate%20between%20genuine%20errors%20and%20acts%20of%20negligence%20by%20medical%20practitioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20points%20from%20the%20Jacob%20Mathew%20case%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Gross%20Negligence%20Standard%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0The%20court%20held%20that%20for%20a%20doctor%20to%20be%20held%20criminally%20liable%2C%20the%20negligence%20should%20be%20of%20such%20a%20high%20degree%20as%20to%20amount%20to%20gross%20negligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Intentional%20Acts%20or%20Omissions%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0The%20court%20clarified%20that%20criminal%20liability%20would%20arise%20only%20if%20a%20medical%20professional%E2%80%99s%20act%20or%20omission%20is%20so%20reckless%20or%20negligent%20that%20it%20can%20be%20equated%20with%20a%20criminal%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Professional%20Standards%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0The%20court%20emphasised%20the%20importance%20of%20adhering%20to%20high%20professional%20standards%20and%20medical%20ethics%2C%20and%20that%20a%20breach%20of%20these%20standards%20could%20be%20a%20ground%20for%20criminal%20liability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Expert%20Opinion%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0The%20court%20highlighted%20the%20significance%20of%20obtaining%20expert%20opinion%20to%20establish%20negligence%2C%20and%20that%20the%20opinion%20should%20be%20given%20by%20a%20doctor%20in%20the%20same%20field%20as%20the%20one%20being%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Jacob%20Mathew%20case%20has%20since%20been%20cited%20in%20various%20judgements%20related%20to%20medical%20negligence%20in%20India%20and%20provided%20a%20framework%20for%20determining%20when%20criminal%20liability%20may%20be%20imposed%20on%20medical%20practitioners%20for%20their%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20does%20it%20mean%20for%20patients%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Asokan%20added%20that%20there%20is%20always%20the%20possibility%20of%20seeking%20civil%20compensation%20in%20cases%20of%20negligence%2C%20which%20aligns%20with%20what%20is%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Claw%20of%20thoughts%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20medical%20profession%20falls%20within%20the%20purview%20of%20this%20law%20and%20while%20we%20adhere%20to%20it%2C%20our%20contention%20lies%20in%20distinguishing%20it%20from%20criminal%20negligence.%20In%20the%20realm%20of%20criminal%20law%2C%20intent%20plays%20a%20crucial%20role%2C%20often%20denoted%20by%20the%20Latin%20term%20%E2%80%98mens%20rea%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Dr%20Asokan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20explained%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20exists%20a%20distinction%20between%20a%20doctor-patient%20relationship%20and%20instances%20of%20medical%20negligence%20or%20accidents%2C%20such%20as%20unpredictable%20events%2C%20like%20anaesthetic%20deaths%2C%20which%20are%20commonly%20referred%20to%20as%20medical%20accidents.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20IMA%E2%80%99s%20stance%20emphasised%20that%20the%20medical%20profession%20complies%20with%20the%20law%20of%20civil%20compensation%20and%20the%20law%20of%20thoughts%2C%20but%20it%20rejects%20the%20notion%20of%20criminal%20negligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20position%20has%20found%20support%20from%20the%20Home%20Minister%20and%20the%20Government%20of%20India.%20On%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20Parliament%2C%20the%20Home%20Minister%20expressed%20intention%20to%20amend%20the%20law%2C%20stating%20that%20in%20the%20context%20of%20treatment%2C%20there%20is%20no%20murder%20involved%2C%20and%20doctors%20can%20be%20exempted.%20This%20statement%20marks%20a%20departure%20from%20what%20the%20government%20had%20previously%20articulated%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Dr%20Asokan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20civil%20liabilities%2C%20the%20consumer%20commission%20is%20the%20available%20platform%20for%20patients%20who%20find%20doctors%20and%20hospitals%20liable%20for%20negligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20hospitals%20and%20doctors%20are%20covered%20under%20indemnity%20insurance%2C%20a%20financial%20arrangement%20that%20provides%20protection%20against%20potential%20losses%20or%20damages%20by%20compensating%20doctors%20for%20covered%20liabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Dr%20Asokan%2C%20the%20new%20law%20is%20advantageous%20for%20both%20doctors%20and%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20event%20of%20a%20loss%2C%20patients%E2%80%99%20families%20can%20pursue%20civil%20suits%20without%20doctors%20being%20perceived%20as%20criminals%20or%20murderers.%20This%20instils%20confidence%20in%20doctors%2C%20especially%20in%20critical%20situations%2C%20eliminating%20the%20fear%20of%20imprisonment%20and%20allowing%20them%20to%20take%20calculated%20risks.%20The%20beneficiaries%20here%20are%20both%20the%20patient%20and%20the%20doctor%2C%20making%20it%20a%20positive%20development%20for%20public%20health%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr%20Asokan%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2F%5C%22%3E%20South%20First%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20Read%20the%20original%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2Fhealth%2Fima-hails-legal-safeguard-doctors-gratitude-as-new-legislation-curbs-criminal-prosecution-in-cases-of-medical-negligence%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703420441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F01124355%2FDYF-camp.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhy-is-the-ima-cheering-if-doctors-are-still-punishable-for-medical-negligence%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20IMA%20is%20happy%20that%20the%20new%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20differentiates%20medical%20negligence%20from%20criminal%20offence%2C%20and%20offers%20a%20less%20harsh%20punishment.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhy-is-the-ima-cheering-if-doctors-are-still-punishable-for-medical-negligence%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Some%20people%20go%20all%20in%20and%20sell%20everything'%3A%20People%20who've%20lived%20and%20sailed%20full-time%20on%20a%20boat%20shared%20how%20they%20did%20it%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sunset%20on%20the%20open%20ocean%20with%20beautiful%20sailboat.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658630701c5c7b8c9a0bc16d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJustin%20Lewis%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBusiness