0Feels%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Should%20Review%20its%20Article%20370%20Judgment%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F24111435%2FLokur-1.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20highly%20regarded%20former%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20Justice%20Madan%20Lokur%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-sc-erred-on-article-370-should-review-its-verdict-justice-madan-lokur%5C%22%3Erecently%20told%20Karan%20Thapar%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20erred%20and%20cannot%20be%20proud%20of%20its%20Kashmir%20judgement%2C%20in%20which%20it%20upheld%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20move%20to%20read%20down%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%20Justice%20Lokur%20also%20described%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-kashmir-article-370-verdict%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%20judgement%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20complex%20and%20complicated%20adding%20it%E2%80%99s%20at%20least%20200%20pages%20too%20long.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20full%20text%20of%20the%20talk%20is%20below%20and%20has%20been%20edited%20lightly%20for%20style%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Hello%20and%20welcome%20to%20a%20special%20interview%20for%20The%20Wire.%20There%E2%80%99s%20no%20doubt%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Kashmir%20judgments%20of%20Monday%2C%20the%2011th%2C%20are%20complicated%20and%20for%20some%20people%20very%20difficult%20to%20understand.%20They%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20widely%20anticipated%20and%20long%20expected.%20But%20that%20makes%20understanding%20them%20even%20more%20important.%20So%20joining%20me%20today%20to%20help%20explain%20the%20judgments%20is%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20foremost%20senior%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20highly%20regarded%20and%20well-regarded%20Justice%20Madan%20Lokur.%20Will%20help%20us%20both%20understand%20the%20judgments%20as%20well%20as%20their%20implications%20and%20indeed%20their%20complications.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJustice%20Lokur%2C%20let%20me%20start%20with%20a%20simple%20general%20question.%20I%E2%80%99ll%20come%20to%20the%20details%20after%20that.%20How%20do%20you%20view%2C%20in%20an%20overall%20sense%2C%20the%20Kashmir%20judgments%20that%20were%20announced%20on%20Monday%2C%20the%2011th%3F%20Are%20you%20impressed%20by%20the%20judicial%20arguments%20they%20contain%2C%20or%20do%20you%20have%20reservations%20about%20some%20of%20the%20reasoning%20and%20its%20implications%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EMadan%20Lokur%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Yes%2C%20well%2C%20thank%20you%2C%20Karan.%20There%20are%20two%20or%20three%20things.%20One%20is%20that%20the%20case%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20as%20complicated%20as%20the%20judgment%20makes%20it%20out%20to%20be.%20I%20think%20that%20maybe%20200%20or%20maybe%20250%20pages%20of%20the%20judgment%20were%20not%20necessary%2C%20unless%20I%E2%80%99ve%20missed%20something.%20I%E2%80%99ve%20not%20been%20able%20to%20connect%20the%20dots%20or%20something.%20But%20I%20think%20maybe%20200%20or%20250%20judgments%20could%20be%20straight%20away%20taken%20out.%20Now%2C%20in%20a%20judgment%2C%20I%20would%20expect%20that%20when%20you%20are%20referring%20to%20something%20which%20is%20not%20readily%20available%2C%20the%20constitution%20of%20India%20is%20readily%20available%2C%20a%20law%20enacted%20by%20Parliament%20is%20readily%20available.%20But%20when%20you%E2%80%99re%20talking%20about%20a%20constitutional%20order%20which%20has%20been%20passed%20with%20reference%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20readily%20available.%20I%20mean%2C%20you%20have%20to%20go%20through%20the%20internet%20and%20get%20that%2C%20and%20some%20facts%20pertaining%20to%20the%20constitutional%20order%2C%20they%20were%20not%20a%20part%20of%20the%20judgment.%20So%20then%20it%20becomes%20very%20difficult%20when%20you%E2%80%99re%20reading%20the%20judgment%2C%20and%20then%20you%20want%20to%20refer%20to%20something.%20You%20have%20to%20go%20to%20your%20computer%20and%20try%20and%20look%20at%20the%20constitutional%20order%20and%20see%20what%20it%20says.%20So%20these%20are%20things%20which%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20go%20through%20the%20judgment.%20Now%2C%20as%20far%20as%20the%20submissions%20are%20concerned%20and%20the%20reasoning%20is%20concerned%2C%20like%20I%20said%2C%20if%20you%20take%20out%20200%20or%20250%20pages%2C%20then%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20become%20so%20complicated%2C%20then%20the%20issues%20get%20narrowed%20down.%20In%20fact%2C%20they%20were%20narrowed%20down%20at%20some%20part%20of%20the%20judgment.%20And%20if%20you%20look%20at%20it%20from%20that%20point%20of%20view%2C%20well%2C%20the%20reasoning%20you%20could%20disagree%20with%20is%20right.%20You%2C%20I%20mean%2C%20in%20any%20case%2C%20given%20the%20same%20facts%2C%20judges%20disagree.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20So%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20saying%20in%20terms%20of%20your%20overall%20view%20is%20a)%20it%20could%20have%20been%20pages%20shorter%2C%20which%20would%20have%20made%20it%20easier%20to%20understand%2C%20b)%20it%20could%20have%20referred%20to%20many%20of%20the%20things%20that%20it%20talks%20about%20rather%20than%20requiring%20you%20to%20have%20to%20cross-reference%20them%20from%20computers.%20So%20it%E2%80%99s%20neither%20easily%20written%20nor%20easy%20to%20fully%20follow.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yes.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20took%20me%20a%20long%20time%20to%20understand%20the%20judgment%20because%20it%20was%20so%20complicated.%20Then%20you%20keep%20going%20back%20and%20forth%2C%20forth%20and%20back.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20So%20they%E2%80%99ve%20made%20it%20deliberately%20difficult%20to%20follow.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20whether%20they%20made%20it%20deliberately%20difficult%2C%20but%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20follow.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjustice-nariman-speech-election-commission-article-370-supreme-court-bbc-media%5C%22%3EBBC%20Raid%2C%20Article%20370%2C%20Election%20Commission%2C%20Governors%3A%20Justice%20Nariman%20Tears%20Into%20Modi%20Govt%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Let%E2%80%99s%20then%2C%20with%20that%20as%20the%20background%2C%20come%20to%20the%20details.%20And%20because%20they%E2%80%99re%20complicated%2C%20as%20you%20say%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20take%20the%20question%20slowly.%20More%20importantly%2C%20with%20your%20permission%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20read%20the%20questions%20because%20I%20think%20in%20this%20instance%2C%20at%20least%20terminology%20is%20important.%20I%20should%20be%20using%20the%20right%20words%20rather%20than%20just%20any%20word%20that%20fits%20in.%20Now%2C%20first%20of%20all%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20discovered%20that%20%E2%80%9Calthough%20the%20petitioners%20challenged%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20assembly%20and%20the%20imposition%20of%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20Rule%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20acknowledges%20that%20both%20were%20challenged%2C%20the%20court%20actually%20failed%20to%20discuss%20the%20challenge%20and%20therefore%20to%20suspend%20it.%20The%20petitioners%20had%20argued%20that%20an%20alternate%20government%20was%20viable%20and%20therefore%20the%20dissolution%20and%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20were%20unconstitutional.%20Had%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20agreed%20with%20this%20challenge%2C%20everything%20that%20followed%20the%20dissolution%20and%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20such%20as%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20such%20as%20abrogation%20of%20article%2C%20such%20as%20the%20reorganization%20of%20the%20state%2C%20all%20of%20that%20would%20have%20been%20invalid.%E2%80%9D%20So%20let%20me%20start%20by%20asking%2C%20was%20this%20a%20lapse%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20part%20not%20to%20directly%20challenge%2C%20not%20to%20directly%20tackle%20this%20challenge%3F%20And%20if%20it%20was%20a%20lapse%2C%20how%20serious%20a%20lapse%20was%20it%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20notes%20in%20paragraph%2019%2C%20I%20think%2C%20that%20the%20proclamation%20issued%20by%20the%20governor%20was%20under%20challenge.%20And%20I%20think%20in%20the%20same%20paragraph%20or%20maybe%20a%20paragraph%20or%20two%20later%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20notes%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20proclamation%20issued%20by%20the%20president%20was%20also%20under%20challenge.%E2%80%9D%20Two%20proclamations%20were%20both%20under%20challenge.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20say%20anything%20about%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20assembly.%20Right%2C%20so%20this%20is%20a%20fact%20which%20has%20not%20come%20on%20record.%20But%20I%20assume%20that%20the%20assembly%20was%20dissolved%20at%20some%20point%20in%20time%20because%20they%E2%80%99ve%20given%20a%20direction%20that%20elections%20should%20be%20held.%20So%20I%E2%80%99m%20assuming%20that%20the%20assembly%20was%20dissolved%20at%20some%20point%20in%20time.%20Now%2C%20so%20far%20as%20the%20proclamation%20issued%20by%20the%20governor%20is%20concerned%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20didn%E2%80%99t%20go%20into%20it.%20Now%20that%20was%20the%20first%20step%2C%20so%20to%20speak.%20The%20first%20thing%20that%20happened%20was%20after%20the%20resignation%20of%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20the%20judgment%20records%20that%20on%20the%20next%20day%20the%20governor%20issued%20the%20proclamation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Dissolving%20the%20assembly%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20whether%20it%20was%20dissolving%20the%20assembly%2C%20but%20imposing%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule.%20Okay%2C%20so%20once%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20was%20imposed%2C%20the%20argument%20also%20of%20the%20petitioners%20was%20that%20listen%2C%20we%E2%80%99d%20been%20telling%20the%20governor%20even%20after%20the%20resignation%20that%20we%20can%20form%20the%20government.%20The%20coalition%20partner%20may%20have%20backed%20out%2C%20but%20we%20can%20still%20form%20the%20government.%20Now%20that%20opportunity%20does%20not%20seem%20to%20have%20been%20given%20by%20the%20governor%2C%20and%20the%20next%20day%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20was%20imposed.%20Now%20the%20argument%20was%20that%20there%20was%20no%20material%20before%20you%20to%20impose%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule.%20Why%20should%20you%20impose%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20when%20we%20can%20tell%20you%20that%20we%20are%20in%20a%20position%20to%20form%20the%20government%3F%20Give%20us%20a%20chance%20to%20form%20the%20government.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20didn%E2%80%99t%20look%20into%20that%2C%20unfortunately.%20Now%20with%20regard%20to%20what%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20was%20that%20subsequent%20events%20were%20challenged.%20All%20subsequent%20events%20were%20challenged%2C%20but%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20the%20challenge%20to%20the%20proclamation%20was%20given%20up.%20Then%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20presidential%20proclamations%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20says%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20looking%20into%20it%2C%20and%20they%20give%20two%20or%20three%20reasons.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20I%E2%80%99ll%20come%20to%20the%20presidential%20proclamations%20in%20a%20moment%E2%80%99s%20time.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20first%20focus%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20look%20into%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20proclamation%20declaring%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule.%20As%20you%20pointed%20out%2C%20Mehbooba%20Mufti%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20said%20the%20declaration%20of%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20is%20improper%20and%20unconstitutional%20because%20an%20alternate%20government%20can%20be%20formed.%20Give%20me%20time%3B%20I%E2%80%99ll%20form%20it.%20She%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20given%20time%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20the%20governor%20was%20imposed%20at%20a%20stage%20when%20an%20alternative%20could%20have%20been%20brought%20into%20being%20in%20the%20form%20of%20government.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20was%20wrong.%20And%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20saying%2C%20if%20I%20understand%20correctly%2C%20is%20if%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20looked%20into%20the%20declaration%20of%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20it%20could%20have%20concluded%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20was%20prematurely%20and%20wrongly%20declared.%20And%20if%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20case%2C%20everything%20that%20follows%20after%20the%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20will%20become%20invalid.%20Therefore%2C%20abrogation%20of%20370%20would%20become%20invalid%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20reorganization%20of%20the%20states%20would%20become%20invalid.%20Yeah%2C%20so%20failure%20to%20look%20into%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20meant%20that%20you%20could%20have%20checked%20the%20process%20there%20and%20then%2C%20but%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yes%2C%20the%20next%20day%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20turns%20out.%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20was%20imposed%2C%20okay.%20This%20was%2C%20if%20I%20remember%20correctly%2C%20sometime%20on%20June%2018%20or%2019%20or%20something.%20Now%20the%20notifications%20that%20were%20under%20challenge%20to%20the%20constitutional%20orders%20were%20issued%20on%20the%205th%20of%20August%2C%20so%20between%20the%2018th%20or%2019th%20of%20June%20and%20the%205th%20of%20August%2C%20there%20was%20time%20in%20theory%20for%20somebody%20to%20form%20the%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20That%20was%20the%20key%20of%20the%20challenge%2C%20and%20by%20not%20looking%20at%20that%20challenge%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20failed%20to%20take%20a%20step%20that%20might%20have%20led%20to%20the%20conclusion%20the%20abrogation%20was%20wrong%2C%20the%20reorganization%20was%20wrong.%20Because%20if%20a%20new%20government%20could%20be%20formed%2C%20there%E2%80%99d%20be%20no%20opportunity%20for%20any%20of%20these%20things.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yes%2C%20yes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20So%20we%E2%80%99re%20agreed%20this%20is%20a%20very%20serious%20lapse%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20part.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Let%E2%80%99s%20then%20come%20to%20the%20second%20important%20thing.%20This%20is%20the%20Court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20uphold%20what%20is%20popularly%20called%20the%20%E2%80%9Cabrogation%20of%20Article%20370%E2%80%9D.%20Now%2C%20this%20is%20particularly%20complicated%2C%20so%20I%E2%80%99ll%20go%20through%20it%20very%20carefully%20with%20you.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20the%20majority%20judgment%20written%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20Chandra%20says%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20critical%20part%20of%20constitutional%20Order%20272%2C%20which%20reads%20down%20Article%20370%E2%80%99s%20ultra%20vires%20because%20it%20wrongly%20used%20Article%20367%20to%20interpret%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20as%20a%20legislative%20assembly.%20Yeah%2C%20and%20since%20the%20process%20that%20the%20government%20had%20used%20to%20abrogate%20370%20was%20precisely%20this%20process%2C%20the%20court%20should%20have%20actually%20struck%20down%20the%20abrogation.%20But%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t.%20What%20the%20court%20instead%20said%20was%20that%20because%20Article%20370%20can%20be%20read%20down%20by%20use%20of%20Clause%203%2C%20therefore%20it%20upheld%20what%20the%20government%20did.%20And%20in%20effect%2C%20what%20that%20means%20is%20that%20the%20Court%20ruled%20that%20what%20the%20government%20did%20was%20wrongly%20done%20but%20if%20it%20had%20been%20done%20differently%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20correct.%20And%20therefore%2C%20it%20gave%20the%20government%20the%20effective%20benefit%20of%20the%20doubt.%20Now%2C%20to%20my%20mind%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20convoluted%20sort%20of%20logic.%20How%20do%20you%20view%20it%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yeah%2C%20the%20constitutional%20Order%20272%2C%20right%3F%20It%20had%20three%20things%20if%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20mind%20if%20I%20can%20just%20go%20through%20it.%20It%20said%2C%20first%20of%20all%2C%20that%20the%20constitution%20of%20India%20is%20applied%20in%20full%20to%20the%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20like%20it%20applies%20in%20full%20to%20every%20other%20state%20in%20the%20country.%20Second%2C%20it%20said%20that%20the%20expression%20Constituent%20Assembly%20in%20Clause%203%20of%20Section%20370%20should%20be%20read%20as%20legislative%20assembly%20because%20of%20an%20amendment%20made%20in%20Article%20367%2C%20which%20deals%20with%20the%20interpretation%20of%20the%20constitution.%20The%20third%20thing%20which%20the%20constitutional%20Order%20272%20says%20is%20that%20all%20past%20constitutional%20orders%20are%20obliterated%20or%20revoked%20or%20abrogated%20or%20whatever.%20Now%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20that%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20read%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20to%20mean%20legislative%20assembly.%20Why%20can%E2%80%99t%20you%20do%20that%3F%20Because%20you%20are%20then%20amending%20Clause%203%20of%20Section%2037%20of%20Article%20370.%20You%20cannot%20amend%20Clause%203%20or%20even%20Article%20370%20without%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20state%20government.%20So%2C%20therefore%2C%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20read%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20to%20mean%20legislative%20assembly.%20But%20they%20said%20that%20the%20constitution%20of%20India%20can%20be%20applied%20in%20full%20to%20the%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20Now%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20that%E2%80%99s%20correct%20because%20if%20that%20was%20correct%2C%20then%20why%20make%20this%20amendment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Absolutely%2C%20and%20if%20the%20amendment%20is%20wrong%2C%20yeah%2C%20and%20the%20amendment%20is%20the%20basis%20upon%20which%20the%20government%20is%20trying%20to%20amend%20370%2C%20yeah%2C%20then%20the%20attempt%20to%20amend%20falls%20by%20the%20wayside.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yes%2C%20I%20mean%20Article%20379%20could%20not%20have%20been%20amended%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20be%20clear%20about%20it.%20But%20there%2C%20I%20think%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20falters%2C%20they%E2%80%99ve%20come%20to%20some%20conclusions%20which%20I%E2%80%99m%20unable%20to%20understand%20how%20they%E2%80%99ve%20come%20to.%20For%20example%2C%20they%20say%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20all%20right%20if%20the%20constitution%20of%20India%20is%20applied%20to%20the%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20Now%2C%20if%20it%20was%20so%20simple%2C%20it%20could%20have%20been%20done%20without%20all%20this%20rigmarole.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Absolutely%2C%20and%20to%20my%20mind%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20a%20layman%2C%20but%20the%20simple%20thing%20is%20the%20procedure%20that%20the%20government%20used%20to%20amend%20370%20was%20to%20reinterpret%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20to%20make%20it%20a%20legislative%20assembly.%20Yeah%2C%20the%20second%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20says%20that%E2%80%99s%20ultra%20vires%2C%20then%20the%20procedure%20the%20government%20has%20used%20becomes%20ultra%20vires%2C%20yeah%2C%20and%20therefore%20it%20follows%20that%20you%20must%20strike%20down%20what%20the%20government%20has%20done%2C%20right%3F%20But%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t.