20Pradesh%20and%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20were%20done%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20recommendations%20made%20by%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly.%20Okay%2C%20so%20that%E2%80%99s%20fine%2C%20but%20now%20what%20the%20judgment%20says%20is%20that%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20even%20necessary.%20Quite%20right%2C%20okay%2C%20so%20if%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20necessary%2C%20then%20what%20happens%20to%20federalism%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20A%20nasty%20government%2C%20and%20maybe%20the%20word%20nasty%20is%20a%20bit%20editorializing%2C%20but%20a%20determined%20government%20can%20say%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20state%3B%20we%E2%80%99re%20determined%20to%20teach%20the%20government%20in%20Bengal%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20and%20Kerala%20a%20lesson.%20We%20will%20declare%20the%20president%E2%80%99s%20rule.%20We%20will%20then%20use%20the%20power%20of%20parliament%2C%20which%20has%20assumed%20the%20power%20of%20the%20assembly%2C%20to%20divide%20the%20state%20into%20two%20and%20reduce%20both%20hubs%20to%20Union%20territory%20status.%20And%20there%E2%80%99s%20nothing%20anyone%20can%20do%20because%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20set%20a%20precedent%2C%20yeah%2C%20which%20is%20why%20Mr.%20Alok%20Kumar%20Prasanna%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CFederalism%20has%20been%20effectively%20threatened%20by%20what%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20decided%20in%20this%20case.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yeah%2C%20yeah.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20You%20agree%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yeah%2C%20yeah%2C%20except%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20have%20to%20decide%20it.%20I%20mean%20if%20they%20keep%20shirking%20the%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20They%20shook%20it%20once%3B%20they%20could%20shirk%20it%20again%20and%20agai